# HubSpot CMS React (landing-page-theme)

## Module structure

- One module per folder under `components/modules/<ModuleName>/`: `index.tsx`, `fields.tsx`, optional `*.module.css`, `_locales/`.
- Reusable field groups live in `components/fieldLibrary/`; export from `components/fieldLibrary/index.ts`.
- Shared UI in `components/<Name>Component/` when used across modules.

## Patterns in this repo

- Use **CSS modules** (`*.module.css`) for module and component styles.
- Use existing helpers: `create-component`, `content-fields`, `classnames` under `components/utils/`.
- Types live under `components/types/` (`fields.ts`, `modules.ts`, `components.ts`).

## HubSpot specifics

- Module field definitions belong in `fields.tsx` (and theme-level defaults in `fields.json` when appropriate).
- Do not invent HubSpot field APIs; match patterns from existing modules (e.g. Button, GettingStarted).
- Prefer small, focused changes; avoid drive-by refactors outside the task scope.

## Testing

- Add or update Vitest tests for utils under `components/utils/` when changing shared logic.
- Run `npm test` from the repo root before considering utils work done.
